article.headline: Elon University 81, Furman 77 (OT)
article.story: ELON, N.C. (AP) -- Montell Watson scored 19 points, including the basket that sent the game into overtime, to lead Elon to an 81-77 victory over Furman in a Southern Conference game Monday night. Chris Chalko scored 15 points while LeVonn Jordan added 13 for the Phoenix (10-9, 6-0 Southern Conference). Moussa Diagne led Furman (11-7, 5-2) with 19 points. Robby Bostain had 15; Eric Webb, 14; and George Brozos, 11. Watson's 3-pointer with 33 seconds left in regulation tied the score at 60-60 and sent the game into overtime. Bostain put Furman up 62-60 on a jumper with 4:38 to go in overtime. Elon responded with a 14-1 surge to build a 74-63 lead on Chalko's two free throws. The Paladins then went on a 12-4 run to pull with 78-75 on a 3-pointer by Brozos with 16 seconds left. After a pair of free throws by Elon's Brian Waters, Bostain hit another 3-pointer to bring Furman within 80-77 with seven seconds left. With four seconds remaining, Watson hit the second of two free throw attempts to clinch the Phoenix victory.
